column17: The attack took place in Tirana.
column18: 07/16/2009: On Thursday night at about 2300, in Tirana, Tirane, Albania, an improvised explosive device attached underneath a car with Tirana registration plates, exploded in front of the Albanian Parliament, damaging two nearby buildings and the car but causing no causalities. No motive for the attack was reported and no group has claimed responsibility.
column64: The specific motive for the attack is unknown.
column97: An improvised explosive device was used in the attack.
column108: The attack caused property damage to two buildings and one car.
column128: One Vehicle Damaged in IED Attack in Tirana

column18: 12/13/2013: Police found an explosive device under Besnik Dervishi's car in an unknown location in Albania. Dervishi, a regional governor, was unharmed in the attack as the device was defused before it could detonate. No group claimed responsibility for the incident.
column97: A 200 gram explosive made from C4, two detonators, a cell phone, and attached to a car was used in the attack.
